==English==

===Etymology===
From Greek ''epopteia'': variously defined as supervision, beholding, revelation, unveiling; the name of a [[sacred]] [[rite]] of the [[w:Eleusinian Mysteries | Eleusinian Mysteries]].

===Noun===
;epopt
#An [[initiate]] in the Eleusinian Mysteries; one who has attended the [[epopteia]].
#One [[instruct]]ed in the [[mystery | mysteries]] of a [[secret]] [[system]].

===Adjective===
;epoptic
#Of or relating to an epopt.
#Of or relating to the mysteries known to an epopt.